PRODUCT SPECIFICATION — HYDRAULIC BRAKE SYSTEM MODULE
Document No: ENG-SPEC-0042-Rev3
Status: APPROVED
Owner: Engineering Dept.
Approved: 2026-03-14

1. SCOPE
This specification defines the requirements for the hydraulic brake system module (BSM-400 series) for passenger vehicle applications.

2. APPLICABLE STANDARDS
- ISO 26262 (Functional Safety)
- IATF 16949 (Quality Management)
- ECE R13 (Brake Performance)
- SAE J1939 (CAN Interface)

3. PERFORMANCE REQUIREMENTS
3.1 Operating Pressure: 8–180 bar
3.2 Temperature Range: -40°C to +120°C
3.3 Service Life: 300,000 km / 15 years
3.4 Brake response time: ≤ 100ms from signal to hydraulic actuation
3.5 Fluid: DOT 4 and DOT 5.1 compatible

4. INTERFACE REQUIREMENTS
4.1 Electrical: 12V CAN bus (SAE J1939), 3x connectors (AMP Superseal)
4.2 Mechanical: ISO 4038 mounting, M12 bolts, torque 45 Nm ±5%
4.3 Hydraulic: M10x1 hydraulic fittings, max torque 25 Nm

5. TESTING REQUIREMENTS
5.1 Pressure cycling test: 5,000,000 cycles at rated pressure
5.2 Thermal shock test: -40°C to +120°C, 500 cycles
5.3 Vibration: per ISO 16750-3, Category D (heavy truck)
5.4 IP Rating: IP69K

6. PACKAGING & LOGISTICS
- Single unit packaging: foam-lined cardboard box
- Label: Part number, serial number, QR code (GS1)
- Shelf life: 24 months from production date

7. CHANGE HISTORY
Rev1: Initial release (2024-01)
Rev2: Updated IP rating from IP67 to IP69K (2025-06)
Rev3: Added SAE J1939 CAN interface requirement (2026-03)
